An Act relative to establishing a food justice frontline.
Be it enacted by the Senate and House of Representatives in General Court assembled, and by the authority
of the same, as follows:
1 SECTION 1. Chapter 18 of the General Laws is hereby amended by inserting after
2 section 2B the following 2 sections:
3 Section 2C. (a) As used in this section, the following words shall have the following
4 meanings, unless the context clearly requires otherwise.
5 “Department”, the department of transitional assistance.
6 “Food security job”, any financially compensated work involving food production, food
7 distribution, food preparation, or food delivery for food insecure Massachusetts residents.
8 “Nonprofit food security organization”, an organization that is exempt from taxation
9 under section 501(c) of the Internal Revenue Code and that has programs which: (1) provide land
10 to low- and moderate-income individuals for agricultural production; or (2) has programs which
11 provide food security jobs to low- and moderate-income individuals, including, but not limited
12 to, food production jobs, food distribution jobs, food preparation jobs, and food delivery jobs.
